 Black Nitride/QPQ: This is an extreme case hardening process which turns the steel black and hardens the surface of the steel and extends the life of the product. QPQ stands for Quench Polish Quench. This process is now commonly used in the industry. The Black Nitride is coated by H&M who own the trademark, "Black Nitride". Only the best here.
The Barrel is a Green Mountain Barrel which was machined by KAK industries. It is 416 stainless with a 1/10 twist. Chambered in 308 winwhich also will accept 7.62 nato. It is medium contour with a DPMS LR308 extension matte blasted grey finish.
